<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-19T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-19T15:00:00-05:00" n="555" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d555">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">Conference files, lot 60 D 627, <gloss target="#t_CF1">CF</gloss> 242</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">United States
                                        Delegation</gloss></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d555fn1">Drafted
                                    by <persName corresp="#p_OCRL1">O’Connor</persName> of <gloss target="#t_S1">S</gloss>.</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>priority</hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-19T16:00:00-04:00">May 19, 1954—4
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><gloss target="#t_Tedul1">Tedul</gloss> 88. For Under Secretary from
                                Secretary. A news ticker report from London indicates British
                                sources have informed the press there re agreement on five-power
                                talks. In view of firm <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> agreement
                                set forth in <gloss target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 84<note n="2" xml:id="d555fn2">Dated May 18, <ref target="#pg_841">p.
                                        841</ref>.</note> that there would be no publicity
                                whatsoever and <pb facs="0883" n="857" xml:id="pg_857"/> no
                                announcement to the press I find this development most
                                disheartening. Unless you perceive objection, please mention this to
                                    <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> and tell him ticker
                                report on information given out in London arrived at precise time
                                that President was going over his proposal which specifically stated
                                nothing would be said to press.</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_DJF1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>